        {
          "id": "CVE-2026-54514",
          "ghsa_id": "GHSA-hgj6-7826-r7m5",
          "severity": "medium",
          "summary": "jackson-databind: InetSocketAddress deserialization triggers eager DNS resolution (SSRF)",
          "description": "## Summary\n`JDKFromStringDeserializer` constructed `InetSocketAddress` with `new InetSocketAddress(host, port)`, which performs eager DNS name resolution for hostname inputs at deserialization time. An application that binds untrusted JSON into a type containing an `InetSocketAddress` field issues an attacker-chosen DNS query during `readValue`, before any application-level validation or connect logic. The fix uses `InetSocketAddress.createUnresolved(host, port)`, deferring DNS to an explicit connect.\n\n## Impact\nAn attacker controlling JSON deserialized into an `InetSocketAddress`-bearing type can force outbound DNS lookups for attacker-chosen hostnames at deserialization time (SSRF / DNS-based out-of-band interaction / internal-resolver probing), purely from binding.\n\n## Affected / Patched (verified via `git tag --contains` on `1f5a103`)\n- 2.18 line: `>= 2.18.0, < 2.18.8` -> fixed in **2.18.8**\n- 2.19-2.21 line: `>= 2.19.0, < 2.21.4` -> fixed in **2.21.4**\n- 3.x line: `>= 3.0.0, < 3.1.4` -> fixed in **3.1.4**\n\n## Severity / CWE\nMaintainer: minor. Reporter: LOW. CWE-918 (SSRF).\n\n## Upstream fix\nFasterXML/jackson-databind#5951 (\"Improve InetSocketAddress deserialization\"). Released 2026-06-04 in 2.18.8 / 2.21.4 / 3.1.4.\n\n## Credits\nOmkhar Arasaratnam (@omkhar) - finder.",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-hgj6-7826-r7m5",
          "affectedDeps": [
            {
              "name": "com.fasterxml.jackson.core:jackson-databind",
              "vulVersions": ">= 2.0.0, < 2.18.8",
              "patchedVersion": "2.18.8"
            },
            {
              "name": "com.fasterxml.jackson.core:jackson-databind",
              "vulVersions": ">= 2.19.0, < 2.21.4",
              "patchedVersion": "2.21.4"
            },
            {
              "name": "com.fasterxml.jackson.core:jackson-databind",
              "vulVersions": ">= 3.0.0, < 3.1.4",
              "patchedVersion": "3.1.4"
            },
            {
              "name": "tools.jackson.core:jackson-databind",
              "vulVersions": ">= 2.19.0, < 2.21.4",
              "patchedVersion": "2.21.4"
            },
            {
              "name": "tools.jackson.core:jackson-databind",
              "vulVersions": ">= 3.0.0, < 3.1.4",
              "patchedVersion": "3.1.4"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "CVE-2026-54515",
          "ghsa_id": "GHSA-5jmj-h7xm-6q6v",
          "severity": "medium",
          "summary": "jackson-databind has case-insensitive deserialization bypasses per-property @JsonIgnoreProperties",
          "description": "## Summary\nIn `BeanDeserializerBase.createContextual()`, per-property `@JsonIgnoreProperties` exclusions are applied by `_handleByNameInclusion()`, producing a `contextual` deserializer whose `BeanPropertyMap` has the ignored properties removed. The subsequent per-property case-insensitivity block (triggered by `@JsonFormat(ACCEPT_CASE_INSENSITIVE_PROPERTIES)`) rebuilds from `this._beanProperties` (the original, unfiltered map) instead of `contextual._beanProperties`, then overwrites the filtered map — restoring every property `_handleByNameInclusion` had just removed. The ignored property becomes writable again.\n\n## Impact\nAn application that both enables case-insensitive matching and relies on per-property `@JsonIgnoreProperties` to keep a field unwritable can have that field set from untrusted JSON (mass-assignment-style write).\n\n## Affected / Patched\nWill be fixed in 2.18.9, 2.21.5, 2.22.1 and 3.1.4.\n\n## Severity / CWE\nMaintainer: minor. Reporter: Moderate. CWE-915.\n\n## Upstream fix\nFasterXML/jackson-databind#5962 (PR #5964, `0e1b0b2`), milestone 3.1.4. Released 2026-06-04.",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-5jmj-h7xm-6q6v",
          "affectedDeps": [
            {
              "name": "com.fasterxml.jackson.core:jackson-databind",
              "vulVersions": ">= 3.1.0, < 3.1.4",
              "patchedVersion": "3.1.4"
            },
            {
              "name": "tools.jackson.core:jackson-databind",
              "vulVersions": ">= 3.1.0, < 3.1.4",
              "patchedVersion": "3.1.4"
            },
            {
              "name": "com.fasterxml.jackson.core:jackson-databind",
              "vulVersions": ">= 2.8.0, < 2.18.9",
              "patchedVersion": "2.18.9"
            },
            {
              "name": "com.fasterxml.jackson.core:jackson-databind",
              "vulVersions": ">= 2.19.0, < 2.21.5",
              "patchedVersion": "2.21.5"
            },
            {
              "name": "com.fasterxml.jackson.core:jackson-databind",
              "vulVersions": ">= 2.22.0, < 2.22.1",
              "patchedVersion": "2.22.1"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
